& [SourceSet] is the bounded research surface
  + [source_001] is Escauriaza, Seregin, and Sverak, L3,infinity-solutions of Navier-Stokes equations and backward uniqueness
    = link: https://www.pdmi.ras.ru/~seregin/Recent%20Publications/engESS3.pdf
    = use: preserves endpoint L3,infinity regularity as a global critical-space theorem
  + [source_002] is Caffarelli-Kohn-Nirenberg seminar notes on Navier-Stokes partial regularity
    = link: https://www.uni-ulm.de/fileadmin/website_uni_ulm/mawi.inst.020/skipper/NotesCKN_Jack_2.pdf
    = use: records scale-invariant local energy and pressure criteria as the local regularity language
  + [source_003] is Barker and Prange, From concentration to quantitative regularity
    = link: https://prange.perso.math.cnrs.fr/papers/survey-concentration-quantreg.pdf
    = use: connects concentration on small scales with quantitative regularity and critical norm behavior
  + [source_004] is Guevara and Nguyen, Local energy bounds and epsilon-regularity criteria for the 3D Navier-Stokes system
    = link: https://www.math.lsu.edu/~pcnguyen/papers_html/Guevara-Phuc-12-29-16.pdf
    = use: develops local energy and pressure-based epsilon-regularity refinements
  + [source_005] is Finite-Scale One-Component Regularity via Harmonic Pressure
    = link: https://arxiv.org/html/2606.08352v1
    = use: recent pressure-decomposition work emphasizing scale-invariant pressure oscillation and harmonic pressure obstructions
  + [source_006] is Quadrupole-Depletion Route to L3 Regularity for 3D Incompressible Navier-Stokes
    = link: https://quantumaetherdynamics.org/papers/Navier_Stokes_Millenium_Puzzle.pdf
    = use: source of the Theta functional and endpoint pressure-work target

& [ResearchFindings] is the theorem-boundary result
  + [finding_001] is epsilon-regularity is the nearest local admission test
    = meaning: a Theta route should be tested by whether it forces smallness of known scale-invariant velocity-pressure quantities on active cylinders
  + [finding_002] is pressure decomposition is central
    = meaning: pressure nonlocality cannot be hidden inside a scalar threshold unless the harmonic/nonlocal pressure part is controlled in the same active-scale frame
  + [finding_003] is concentration-compactness remains relevant but too global
    = meaning: global critical-norm blow-up exclusion identifies the endpoint, while local epsilon criteria identify what a Theta threshold must actually imply
  + [finding_004] is no Theta-to-epsilon theorem was found
    = meaning: no checked source proves that small Theta forces CKN-style local regularity smallness or excludes concentration sequences
  + [finding_005] is new pressure-focused claims remain audit targets
    = meaning: recent pressure-decomposition and regularity claims can sharpen candidate gates but do not become authority without validation

